  <section id="nav" role="tabpanel" class="r-panel is-active" aria-label="Get something done">
    <p class="r-lead">Not sure who handles your question? Find it below and start in the right place instead of getting bounced.</p>
    <div class="r-grid" id="navgrid">

      <div class="r-card" data-text="business start grow self employment entrepreneur company sdc economic development zgamok funding lifelong learning">
        <button type="button"><span>Start or grow a business</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>Business support sits in more than one place, which is the most common reason members get sent in circles. Here is which door is which.</p>
          <div class="r-doors">
            <h4>The three doors</h4>
            <p><b>Sagamok Development Corporation (SDC)</b> offers entrepreneurial support. A good first door for an individual member with a business idea. General Manager: Evan O'Leary.</p>
            <p><b>Band Economic Development</b> is the band-administration door. Manager: Arnelda Bennett (ext. 563).</p>
            <p><b>Z'gamok Enterprises</b> is the resource-sector and contracting arm. The right door for construction and resource work, usually not for a small tech or service start-up.</p>
          </div>
          <p>For start-up support as a member, also ask the Lifelong Learning Centre (705-501-8950) about training and Self-Employment Assistance (see Programs).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="r-card" data-text="job jobs work training school education career coach lifelong learning employment self employment assistance">
        <button type="button"><span>Find a job, training, or schooling</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>Employment, training, and schooling run through Sagamok Education and its Lifelong Learning Centre. Call the Lifelong Learning Centre and ask about training and Self-Employment Assistance; a guidance and career coach can help with training plans and work goals.</p>
          <div class="r-who">
            <span class="r-pill"><b>Lifelong Learning Centre</b> 705-501-8950</span>
            <span class="r-pill"><b>Guidance &amp; Career Coach</b> ext. 242</span>
          </div>
          <p><a href="https://sagamokeducation.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the Sagamok Education site</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="r-card" data-text="house housing rent rental rent to own home build repair self help loan caldwell">
        <button type="button"><span>Apply for housing</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>The Housing Department handles rentals, rent-to-own, self-help loans, and maintenance. To apply or ask where you sit on a list, contact them directly.</p>
          <div class="r-who">
            <span class="r-pill"><b>Housing Director</b> William Caldwell, ext. 130</span>
          </div>
          <p><a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/housing-department" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the Housing Department page</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="r-card" data-text="health nurse doctor medical mental health addictions counselling medical transportation travel home care elder youth wellness">
        <button type="button"><span>See a nurse, get mental-health support, or arrange medical travel</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>The Community Wellness Department runs out of the health centre, Naandwedjige-Gamik.</p>
          <div class="r-who">
            <span class="r-pill"><b>Health centre</b> (705) 865-2171</span>
          </div>
          <p><a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/community-wellness-department" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the Community Wellness page</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="r-card" data-text="child family kids youth advocacy cfau resiliency support prevention nogdawindamin koognaasewin child welfare">
        <button type="button"><span>Get help with a child and family matter</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>Family and Community Support Services helps children, youth, and families through the Child and Family Advocacy Unit and related teams.</p>
          <p>The Child and Family Advocacy Unit is a prevention service for families who are involved with, or at risk of involvement with, Nogdawindamin, the regional child welfare agency for the North Shore First Nations.</p>
          <div class="r-who">
            <span class="r-pill"><b>Child &amp; Family Advocacy Unit</b> (705) 865-3229</span>
          </div>
          <p><a href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/family-and-community-support-services" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open the Family and Community Support page</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="r-card" data-text="status card indian registration band membership estates renee owl member number">
        <button type="button"><span>Ask about status, band membership, or estates</span><span class="r-chev">&#8250;</span></button>
        <div class="r-body">
          <p>Membership, Indian Registration and Estates handles status, band membership, and estates. Contact them directly rather than relying on the online forms.</p>
