  {# ---------------- COUNCIL ---------------- #}
  <section id="council" role="tabpanel" class="r-panel r-council" aria-label="How Council works">
    <p class="r-lead">How Sagamok is governed and where to read the record. This points you to the official source; it does not reproduce or summarize the minutes.</p>

    <h3>Who governs</h3>
    <p>Sagamok is led by an elected Chief and twelve Councillors. Chief Angus Toulouse and Council set direction and oversee the administration that delivers programs and services.</p>

    <h3>How often Council meets</h3>
    <p>Council meets on a regular cycle, roughly every two weeks, about twenty meetings a year, and minutes are written up and posted for members. A steady, frequent schedule means there is a regular written record of decisions.</p>

    <h3>Where to read the minutes</h3>
    <p>Sagamok posts its Chief and Council meeting minutes on its own website. That is the official source.</p>
    <p><a class="btn btn--primary" href="https://www.sagamokanishnawbek.com/meeting-minutes/meeting-minutes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Sagamok's meeting minutes</a></p>

    <h3>How to bring something to Council</h3>
    <p>The path runs through the Council Secretariat (Andrea Hajt-Jacobs, ext. 133) and the Political Office (Wade Owl, ext. 238), who handle correspondence and the agenda.</p>

    <h3>The members' transparency work</h3>
    <p>The treaty-wide and community transparency work that members lead now has its own independent home, the Robinson Huron Treaty Members' Transparency Circle, independent of OIATC. You can <a href="https://rhtcircle.ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">visit the Transparency Circle &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <p class="r-note">A community resource from OIATC, the Ontario Indigenous AI and Technology Council. Independent of Sagamok Chief and Council and its administration, and of the partner organizations named. It describes and links to Sagamok's own programs and record; it does not provide, decide, or reproduce any of them. Main band line: (705) 865-2421.</p>

  <script>
    (function () {
      var root = document.querySelector('[data-module="resources"]');
      if (!root) { return; }
      var tabs = Array.prototype.slice.call(root.querySelectorAll('.r-tab'));
      var panels = {
        nav: root.querySelector('#nav'),
        prog: root.querySelector('#prog'),
        council: root.querySelector('#council'),
      };
      var q = root.querySelector('#r-q');
      var nores = root.querySelector('#r-nores');

      function applySearch() {
        var term = (q.value || '').trim().toLowerCase();
        var active = root.querySelector('.r-panel.is-active');
        if (!active) { return; }
        var cards = Array.prototype.slice.call(active.querySelectorAll('.r-card'));
        if (cards.length === 0) { nores.style.display = 'none'; return; }
        var shown = 0;
        cards.forEach(function (c) {
          var hay = (c.getAttribute('data-text') || '') + ' ' + c.textContent.toLowerCase();
          var match = term === '' || hay.indexOf(term) !== -1;
          c.style.display = match ? '' : 'none';
          if (match) { shown++; }
        });
        nores.style.display = (term !== '' && shown === 0) ? 'block' : 'none';
      }

      function showTab(name) {
        tabs.forEach(function (t) { t.setAttribute('aria-selected', t.getAttribute('data-panel') === name ? 'true' : 'false'); });
        Object.keys(panels).forEach(function (k) { if (panels[k]) { panels[k].classList.toggle('is-active', k === name); } });
        applySearch();
      }

      tabs.forEach(function (t) { t.addEventListener('click', function () { showTab(t.getAttribute('data-panel')); }); });
      root.querySelectorAll('.r-card > button').forEach(function (b) {
        b.addEventListener('click', function () { b.parentNode.classList.toggle('is-open'); });
      });
      root.querySelectorAll('[data-go]').forEach(function (a) {
        a.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
          e.preventDefault();
          showTab(a.getAttribute('data-go'));
          var biz = root.querySelector('#navgrid .r-card');
          if (biz) { biz.classList.add('is-open'); biz.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' }); }
        });
      });
      if (q) { q.addEventListener('input', applySearch); }
    })();
  </script>
